
# PURPOSE : use the following blueprint as a reference to generate a custom test file for a single IRC command, by following the blueprints structure.

# INSTRUCTIONS :
- [DO] Generate 10 test cases using the format above, with RFC [ID] specified above.
- [KEEP-IN-MIND] Generate test-cases only for the '{COMMAND-NAME}' above.
- [KEEP-IN-MIND] Output will be processed by a script by a script so anything that is not a test (following the specified format) should and must always be commented.
- Use auto-join() function that will PASS->NICK->USER to avoid redundancy, of course if they need to be test then dont use it..
# COMMAND-NAME : {JOIN}
# ENVIRONMENT : {PASSWORD:"Alilepro135!"}

=======================================BLUEPRINT===============================================
# IRC Protocol Test Suite
# Based on RFC 2812 and modern IRC protocol extensions
# Format: TestName|ExpectedResponse|Commands

# COMMAND-TO-TEST: {COMMAND-NAME}

# EXAMPLE-TEST:

default PING test|PONG :server1|PASS Alilepro135!\r\nNICK ping_test1\r\nUSER ping1 0 * :Ping Test\r\nPING :server1\r\n

PING with server parameter|PONG :irc.example.com|PASS Alilepro135!\r\nNICK ping_test2\r\nUSER ping2 0 * :Ping Test\r\nPING :irc.example.com\r\n

PING with two server parameters|PONG :irc.example.com|PASS Alilepro135!\r\nNICK ping_test3\r\nUSER ping3 0 * :Ping Test\r\nPING irc.example.com irc.example.net\r\n

PING without parameters|ERROR :No origin specified|PASS Alilepro135!\r\nNICK ping_test4\r\nUSER ping4 0 * :Ping Test\r\nPING\r\n

PING with numeric parameter|PONG :123456|PASS Alilepro135!\r\nNICK ping_test5\r\nUSER ping5 0 * :Ping Test\r\nPING :123456\r\n

PING with special characters|PONG :!@#$%^&*()|PASS Alilepro135!\r\nNICK ping_test6\r\nUSER ping6 0 * :Ping Test\r\nPING :!@#$%^&*()\r\n

PING with maximum length parameter|PONG :aaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaa|PASS Alilepro135!\r\nNICK ping_test7\r\nUSER ping7 0 * :Ping Test\r\nPING :aaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaa\r\n

PING with empty parameter|ERROR :No origin specified|PASS Alilepro135!\r\nNICK ping_test8\r\nUSER ping8 0 * :Ping Test\r\nPING :\r\n

PING with whitespace parameter|PONG :   |PASS Alilepro135!\r\nNICK ping_test9\r\nUSER ping9 0 * :Ping Test\r\nPING :   \r\n

PING with newline character|PONG :\n|PASS Alilepro135!\r\nNICK ping_test10\r\nUSER ping10 0 * :Ping Test\r\nPING :\n\r\n

# Test Case 1: Join a public channel without a key
auto-join() #for redundancy
Join public channel|:test_user!~user@host JOIN #public_channel\r\n:server 353 test_user = #public_channel :@test_user\r\n:server 366 test_user #public_channel :End of /NAMES list.|PASS Alilepro135!\r\nNICK test_user\r\nUSER user 0 * :Test User\r\nJOIN #public_channel\r\n

# Test Case 2: Join a private channel without a key
auto-join()
Join private channel without key|:server 475 test_user #private_channel :Cannot join channel (+k) - bad key|PASS Alilepro135!\r\nNICK test_user\r\nUSER user 0 * :Test User\r\nJOIN #private_channel\r\n

# Test Case 3: Join a private channel with the correct key
auto-join()
Join private channel with correct key|:test_user!~user@host JOIN #private_channel\r\n:server 353 test_user = #private_channel :@test_user\r\n:server 366 test_user #private_channel :End of /NAMES list.|PASS Alilepro135!\r\nNICK test_user\r\nUSER user 0 * :Test User\r\nJOIN #private_channel secretkey\r\n

# Test Case 4: Join an invite-only channel without an invite
auto-join()
Join invite-only channel without invite|:server 473 test_user #invite_only_channel :Cannot join channel (+i) - you must be invited|PASS Alilepro135!\r\nNICK test_user\r\nUSER user 0 * :Test User\r\nJOIN #invite_only_channel\r\n

# Test Case 5: Join an invite-only channel with an invite
auto-join()
Join invite-only channel with invite|:test_user!~user@host JOIN #invite_only_channel\r\n:server 353 test_user = #invite_only_channel :@test_user\r\n:server 366 test_user #invite_only_channel :End of /NAMES list.|PASS Alilepro135!\r\nNICK test_user\r\nUSER user 0 * :Test User\r\nINVITE test_user #invite_only_channel\r\nJOIN #invite_only_channel\r\n


